NCCN Guidelines Version 5.2022 Esophageal and Esophagogastric Junction Cancers

NCCN Guidelines Index Table of Contents Discussion

Updates in Version 5.2022 of the NCCN Guidelines for Esophageal and Esophagogastric Junction Cancers from Version 4.2022 include: MS-1 • The Discussion has been updated to reflect the changes in the algorithm.
Updates in Version 4.2022 of the NCCN Guidelines for Esophageal and Esophagogastric Junction Cancers from Version 3.2022 include: ESOPH-F 3 of 17 Principles of Systemic Therapy for Unresectable Locally Advanced, Recurrent or Metastatic Disease • First-line Therapy; Preferred Regimens; HER2 overexpression negative The following regimens changed from a category 2B to a category 2A recommendation
◊ Fluoropyrimidine (fluorouracil or capecitabine), oxaliplatin, and nivolumab for squamous cell carcinoma ◊ Fluoropyrimidine (fluorouracil or capecitabine), cisplatin, and nivolumab for squamous cell carcinoma

Updates in Version 3.2022 of the NCCN Guidelines for Esophageal and Esophagogastric Junction Cancers from Version 2.2022 include: ESOPH-F 3 of 17 Principles of Systemic Therapy for Unresectable Locally Advanced, Recurrent or Metastatic Disease • First-line Therapy; Preferred Regimens; HER2 overexpression negative; The following regimens were added: Nivolumab and ipilimumab for squamous cell carcinoma Fluoropyrimidine (fluorouracil or capecitabine), oxaliplatin, and nivolumab for squamous cell carcinoma (category 2B) Fluoropyrimidine (fluorouracil or capecitabine), cisplatin, and nivolumab for squamous cell carcinoma (category 2B) • Reference added for the noted regimens: Doki Y, Ajani JA, Kato K, et al. Nivolumab Combination Therapy in Advanced Esophageal
Squamous-Cell Carcinoma. N Engl J Med 2022;386:449-462. ESOPH-F 5 of 17 Principles of Systemic Therapy-Regimens and Dosing Schedules • The dosing schedules were updated to correspond with the new regimens.

Updates in Version 2.2022 of the NCCN Guidelines for Esophageal and Esophagogastric Junction Cancers from Version 1.2022 include: MS-1 • The Discussion has been updated to reflect the changes in the algorithm.

